		<option value="Turkey">Turkey</option>\r\n						<option value="Turkmenistan">Turkmenistan</option>\r\n						<option value="Turks and Caicos Islands">Turks and Caicos Islands</option>\r\n						<option value="Tuvalu">Tuvalu</option>\r\n						<option value="Uganda">Uganda</option>\r\n						<option value="Ukraine">Ukraine</option>\r\n						<option value="United Arab Emirates">United Arab Emirates</option>\r\n						<option value="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</option>\r\n						<option value="United States">United States</option>\r\n						<option value="Uruguay">Uruguay</option>\r\n						<option value="Uzbekistan">Uzbekistan</option>\r\n						<option value="Vanuatu">Vanuatu</option>\r\n						<option value="Vatican City State">Vatican City State (Holy See)</option>\r\n						<option value="Venezuela">Venezuela</option>\r\n						<option value="Viet Nam">Viet Nam</option>\r\n						<option value="Virgin Islands (British)">Virgin Islands (British)</option>\r\n						<option value="Virgin Islands (U.S.)">Virgin Islands (U.S.)</option>\r\n						<option value="Wallis and Futuna Islands">Wallis and Futuna Islands</option>\r\n						<option value="Western Sahara">Western Sahara</option>\r\n						<option value="Yemen">Yemen</option>\r\n						<option value="Yugoslavia">Yugoslavia</option>\r\n						<option value="Zaire">Zaire</option>\r\n						<option value="Zambia">Zambia</option>\r\n						<option value="Zimbabwe">Zimbabwe</option>\r\n					</select>\r\n				</label> \r\n				<label for="Telephone"> \r\n					<br />\r\n					<span><strong>* Telephone:</strong></span><br />\r\n					<input type="text" value="" id="Telephone" name="Telephone" size="40" title="Telephone" /> \r\n				</label> \r\n			</fieldset>\r\n			<fieldset>\r\n				<legend>Additional questions</legend> \r\n				<label for="ra"> \r\n					<br />\r\n					<span>* Keywords on <strong>Research Areas or Special Interests </strong>(these will be shown in the workshop information pack as an aid to networking, \r\n						it is important that you complete this section). :</span><br />\r\n					<textarea title="Your Research Areas or Special Interests " rows="3" cols="51" id="ra" name="ra">\r\n					</textarea>\r\n				</label> \r\n				<label for="sr"> \r\n					<br />\r\n					<span>In addition, do you have any <strong>special requirements</strong>?</span><br />\r\n					<textarea title="Special Requirements, eg wheelchair user or vegetarian" rows="3" cols="51" id="sr" name="sr">\r\n					</textarea>\r\n				</label> \r\n			</fieldset>\r\n			<fieldset>\r\n				<legend>Privacy policy</legend> \r\n				<p>We will use the information you provide only for the specific purpose for which \r\n					you have given it, \r\n					and in accordance with our Data Protection Policy. We will not disclose any such \r\n					personal information \r\n					to a third party without your prior consent. The information you have provided \r\n					here will be printed in\r\n					the workshop park.</p>\r\n				<br />\r\n				<label><input type="checkbox" checked="checked" id="privacy" name="privacy" /> \r\n					I have read and agree to the SPARC privacy policy.\r\n				</label> \r\n			</fieldset>\r\n			<input type="hidden" name="referer" id="referer" value="" /> \r\n			<input type="submit" id="submit" name="submit" value="Submit" title="Submit your Registration" /> \r\n			<input type="reset" value="Reset Form" class="reset" title="Clear Form" /> \r\n		</form>\r\n		<h2>Directions</h2>\r\n		<p>Map: <a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps">http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps</a></p>\r\n		<p>Directions: Travel directions and detailed travel maps to the Holywell Park, \r\n			Loughborough University.<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps/">http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps/</a> </p>\r\n		<p>The campus map shows how to find Holywell Park on Loughborough University campus:<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.lboro.ac.uk/about/map/pages/map-full.html">http://www.lboro.ac.uk/about/map/pages/map-full.html</a> \r\n			and a pdf downloadable version:<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/pdf/imago-area-map.pdf">http://www.welcometoimago.com/pdf/imago-area-map.pdf</a></p>\r\n		<p>By Road: From M1 (Junction 23) or the A6, follow the signs to the University</p>\r\n		<p>By Rail: 90 minutes from London St Pancras. Approximately 10 minutes by taxi or \r\n			bus from Loughborough train station.<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.midlandmainline.com/8">http://www.midlandmainline.com/8</a> </p>\r\n		<p>By Bus: A University Shuttle bus, operated by Kinchbus travels between the \r\n			University and Loughborough''s train station daily.<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.kinchbus.co.uk/7kinchbus.html">http://www.kinchbus.co.uk/7kinchbus.html</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.trentbuses.co.uk/timetables">http://www.trentbuses.co.uk/timetables</a><br />\r\n			Telephone: 01509 816161</p>\r\n		<p>By Air: 8 miles from East Midlands Airport and convenient for Birmingham Airport \r\n			(M42).<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.eastmidlandsairport.com">http://www.eastmidlandsairport.com</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.bhx.co.uk">http://www.bhx.co.uk</a></p>\r\n		<p>On campus accommodation is available for a reasonable price at Burleigh Court, \r\n			Loughborough University. If you need this, you are encouraged<br />\r\n			to book accommodation directly with Burleigh Court, please follow the link<br />\r\n			<a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/accommodation/">http://www.welcometoimago.com/accommodation/</a></p>\r\n	</article> \r\n</div>\r\n', '0000-00-00', 1, 0),
(13, 4, 'Conferences', 'get-involved/conferences.html', '* [Designing Inclusive Interactions](http://www-edc.eng.cam.ac.uk/cwuaat/index.html), The 5th Cambridge Workshop on Universal Access (UA) and Assistive Technology (AT) : CWUAAT 2010\r\nFitzwilliam College, University of Cambridge. Reflects the need to explore the issues and practicalities of design that is intended to extend our active future lives. , Cambridge, 23 - 25 March 2010\r\n            \r\n* [12th International Conference on Mobility and Transport for Elderly and Disabled Persons (TRANSED 2010)](http://www.transed2010.hk/front/home2.html%20for), 1 - 4 June 2010 \r\n\r\n* [Better healthcare through better infrastructure](http://www.haciric.org/Portals/36/Conferences/Call.pdf), This event aims to bring together researchers and practitioners from across disciplines and countries to focus on key challenges in the provision of healthcare infrastructure for the 21st century.\r\nEdinburgh, 22 - 24 September 2010', '0000-00-00', 2, 1),
(14, 5, 'Site Accessibility', 'help/accessibility.html', 'moop', '0000-00-00', 1, 1),
(15, 5, 'Site Map', 'help/site-map.html', 'meep', '0000-00-00', 2, 1),
